10 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to provide
11 protections to tenants by making the charging of a rental application fee an
12 unfair commercial practice, requiring certain rental agreements to be in
13 writing, limiting no-cause evictions and annual rent increases, creating a rental
14 registry, creating the Office of Tenant’s Rights Advocate, providing for the
15 right to counsel in eviction proceedings and the expungement of eviction
16 records, and affording tenants the right to receive notice of a landlord’s intent
17 to sell an apartment building and to negotiate in good faith and purchase the
18 building with a down payment revolving fund administered by the Vermont
19 Housing and Conservation Board. The bill also proposes to add citizenship
20 and immigration status to the existing discrimination prohibitions in public
21 accommodations and unfair housing practices.
